markangle(n=1,radius=15,X,C,B,marker(markinterval(stickframe(n=1),true)));

//label("$24$",.5*(B+X),SE);
label("$56$",.5*(B+C),E);
label("$28$",.5*(A+C),NW);

[/asy]

In rectangle $ABCD$, $AB=5$ and $BC =3$. Points $F$ and $G$ are on $\overline{CD}$ so that $DF = 1$ and $GC=2$. Lines $AF$ and $BG$ intersect at $E$. Find the area of $\triangle AEB$. Express your answer as a common fraction. [asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I,F,G;
A=(0,0);
B=(5,0);
C=(5,3);
D=(0,3);
F=(1,3);
G=(3,3);
I=(1.67,5);
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(A--B--I--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$F$",F,SE);
label("$G$",G,SW);
label("$E$",I,N);
label("1",(0.5,3),N);
label("2",(4,3),N);
label("3",(0,1.5),W);
label("3",(5,1.5),E);
label("5",(2.5,0),S);
[/asy]

